cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of landmark localization in 3D medical images using reinforcement learning. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves learning an optimal policy for a given task. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests the possibility of using artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of temporal difference learning and actor-critic methods, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE).
